	                                    <div class="authorbio">
	                                        <p>Chris loves to build great teams and create great web products. </p>
	                                        <p>Chris has worked in the internet industry since earning his MBA in 1999. He spent his first seven years in product and leadership roles at Yahoo! and AOL. </p>
	                                        <p>In 2006 he moved to Vietnam and became CEO of Vietnam's largest general job website, Vietnamworks.com, which he ran until the company was sold in 2012. </p>
	                                        <p>In 2013 Chris and his partner Anh co-founded ITviec.com with the mission to help IT people in Vietnam build cool products and develop their careers. </p>
	                                        <p>Chris lives in Saigon with his wife and two young children. His favorite quote is "Life is either a daring adventure or nothing" by Helen Keller. His interests include marketing psychology, minimalism, swing dancing, history and leadership.</p>
	                                        <p> <a href="//itviec.com/blog/khi-nao-nen-nhay-viec/">Read Chris's story</a>
	                                        </p>
